This paper describes the application of a neural machine translation model to the prediction of organic chemical reactions. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a parser to generate input tokens for the model, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). The prediction of organic chemical reactions also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of training sets and testing examples, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SD).
